talking about. On a similar note, the \"News and Views\" commentary articles that accompany \"high-impact\" papers are great for giving people unfamiliar with the field a taste of why a certain paper deserves attention.<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p>Come back here and ask!<\/p><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":124,"question_id":122,"up_vote_count":10,"last_edit_date":1323991642},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1059206e9cdfa0201e2f13d43181c730?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":66,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/66/alexander-galkin","reputation":5247,"display_name":"Alexander Galkin"},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":2,"last_activity_date":1323994068,"creation_date":1323993094,"body":"<p>Sorry, I just couldn't help but point out <a href=\"http://rads.stackoverflow.com/amzn/click/0470430664\" rel=\"nofollow\">the following book<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/anAXw.jpg\" alt=\"Molecular biology for dummmies\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Joking aside, every book from this series I read was fantastic. I didn't read this particular one, but I would nonetheless recommend to give it a try. <\/p>\n","answer_id":134,"question_id":122,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1323994068},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1379a548b0ecfcbe5fe13f3bf1984a2b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":51,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/51/mac-cowell","reputation":692,"display_name":"Mac Cowell"},"score":4,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1379a548b0ecfcbe5fe13f3bf1984a2b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":51,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/51/mac-cowell","reputation":692,"display_name":"Mac Cowell"},"score":2,"post_id":144,"edited":false,"creation_date":1324005662,"comment_id":150,"body":"conflict of interest: I helped start diybio.org"}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activ